{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27811c1c-835e-427f-8290-e62d4c11bf68","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files are compiled top-to-bottom, so `Services.fs` (which depends on `Domain.fs`) is listed before `Domain.fs`. I need to swap them.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_aFnF9op0sZz4Hum7sjDdUB","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9b333c11a0924d43b5d8d2131b432894/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9b333c11a0924d43b5d8d2131b432894/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"3579edcd-0712-4b69-afbe-ca96d40131bf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters because the compiler processes files in the order they are listed in the `.fsproj` file. Currently, the order is:\n\n1. `Services.fs` - which `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` - defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` - uses both\n\n`Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, so `Domain.fs` must come first. The correct order should be:\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n\n\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":437,"requestId":"0430:3C3A4F:C4522B:E24ED2:69F2A778"},"id":"87fdfbd2-d870-4a58-a7c9-9a507b41a10a","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:11.477Z","parentId":"fb43602e-e3e5-49ce-b0e4-13b2f02fec6e"}
